review_id:
Era has great atmosphere, the decoration and the lighting make the ambience very cozy, and the glass window makes morning coffee there feel very relaxing.
However, the music choice is inappropriate and too loud, and on busy days, the place does get cramped.

The coffee is great and very decently priced. The staff is very friendly and well-mannered, and orders get done quick with excellent table service.

The tables and chairs are comfortable enough for long sittings.

Best for outdoor work with your laptop  on early (usually quiet) mornings, or bigger groups of friends on the weekend nights.

Maybe not the best costa branch out there but it's definitely my favorite coffee shop in Mansoura. The coffee is amazing but the cold drinks are below average I don't recommend it.

Carrot cake and tiramisu are my favorite dessert plates as they're always fresh and tasty. Sandwiches and croissants are also fresh and worth the try.

Staff are friendly but sometimes too friendly which is weird but that's ok :')
Overall, it's a comfort zone to me.

review_id: Nice place and good coffee. I like the design and atmosphere of this coffee shop. They do also have a good selection of sweets (cheesecakes, croissants, etc). It is a bit pricey though, especially if you order a nondairy substitute for your coffee (almond milk). I wish they offered bigger size cups (I know I said it's a bit pricey, but some of us need a bigger drink, haha) and I would love to see a rewards program in the future, especially since I see they are quickly growing (every 5 drinks, get one drink free, or something along those lines).

review_id:
1. atmosphere, the place looked nice and was clean, nothing too extra 3.5/5

2.service, food took about an hour to arrive, although considering there was like 2 other people there it probably shouldnt have taken this long, waiter was superrrr slow and came by the table to remove our plates after we finished eating for like 4 times when it only needed once, once again the service isnt that bad but definitely not good,they did give us a free icecream at the end as a thank u, 2.5/5

3.food, we ordered the mushroom and chicken white sauce pasta, the pepperoni pizza and the crispy chicken sandwich, pasta was good but nothing too special i've had better, pizza wasnt crispy at all, it was too gooey and the crust was undercooked, pepperoni was sliced which doesnt make a big difference in the taste but it definitely looks better unsliced, the sandwich was dry and didnt have any sauces, chicken wasnt warm and was hard to bite, very dry and hard to chew, wasnt good, overall as someone who doesnt go outside much i was disapointed, definitely could have enjoyed my evening more if i ate somewhere else, however prices were good but i could have payed the same amount somewhere else and got better food, overall experience is 3/5
